    <briefdescription>
<para>Class responsible for handling the stepping action of particles in the simulation. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This class inherits from the G4UserSteppingAction class and implements the UserSteppingAction method. It also provides methods for setting the verbosity level, printing step information, adding hits to collections, performing scattering calculations, and analyzing standard steps.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The <ref refid="classSteppingAction" kindref="compound">SteppingAction</ref> class requires an <ref refid="classEventAction" kindref="compound">EventAction</ref> object and a <ref refid="classGammaRayHelper" kindref="compound">GammaRayHelper</ref> object to be passed to its constructor. These objects are used for event-level actions and gamma ray calculations, respectively. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
